  &lt;p id="eNHVUz"&gt;A new startup created by former Android leaders aims to build an operating system for AI agents. Among them is Hugo Barra, Google’s former VP of Android product management, &lt;a href="https://x.com/hbarra/status/1861414956023062850"&gt;who says&lt;/a&gt; the new company — named “/dev/agents” — will revisit the leaders’ “Android roots.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="nyCfUF"&gt;AI companies are pushing AI agents as the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/10/24266333/ai-agents-assistants-openai-google-deepmind-bots"&gt;next big leap in AI tools&lt;/a&gt;, promising digital assistants that can carry out tasks and make decisions autonomously and with little human input. Companies like &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/21/24275778/microsofts-new-copilot-ai-agents-arrive-next-month"&gt;Microsoft&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/26/24280431/google-project-jarvis-ai-system-computer-using-agent"&gt;Google&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/13/24295879/openai-agent-operator-autonomous-ai"&gt;OpenAI&lt;/a&gt; each have plans to launch some version of this concept as a product in the next few months. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id="T6ZOpz"&gt;
&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-dnt="true" align="center"&gt;
&lt;p lang="en" dir="ltr"&gt;  Excited to announce my new company: /dev/agents. I’m building the next-gen operating system for AI agents, joining my former colleagues &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/hbarra?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw"&gt;@hbarra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/alcor?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw"&gt;@alcor&lt;/a&gt;, and...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
